  • Field Details

    • proteoforms

      private final LinkedHashMap<String,Form> proteoforms
      LinkedHashMap storing all Form instances, i.e. proteoforms, associated with this feature.

    • aminoacidVariants

      private final TreeMap<Integer,LinkedHashMap<String,VariantInformation>> aminoacidVariants
      Hierarchical map structure to store variants wrt. proteoforms. The first layer represents the position on the feature. The second layer represents the variant content.

      Stored positions have to be formatted as X+Y; X is the position on the reference, Y is the possibly inserted position.

    • codingSequence

      private String codingSequence
      The translated reference DNA sequence of the entry.

  • Constructor Details

    • FeatureCoding

      public FeatureCoding(String name, String chromosome, int start, int end, char strand, String type)
      Constructor of FeatureCoding.

      Generates a FeatureCoding with no protein structure associated.

      Parameters:
      name - String representing the internal name of the reference feature to analyze.
      chromosome - String the name of the reference location (contig, chromosome, plasmid) the feature is located on.
      start - Integer The 1-based indexed starting position of the feature on the reference.
      end - Integer The 1-based indexed end position of the feature on the reference.
      strand - The strand orientation (+/-) of the coding feature.
      type - The type (coding or non-coding) of this feature (should also be coding here).

    • setCodingSequence

      public void setCodingSequence(String sequence) throws MusialException
      Sets the specified string as the coding sequence of this instance.
      If the sequence is of nucleotide content, the sequence is translated.
      Parameters:
      sequence - Content to set as coding sequence.
      Throws:
      MusialException - If the translation of a provided nucleotide sequence fails or no nucleotide or aminoacid sequence was provided.
